This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the optimization of hyperparameters in machine learning models. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. The paper also mentions experiments on classification and regression data sets, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these sub-categories often deal with classification and regression tasks. Finally, the paper proposes an extension of SMBO methods, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as optimization algorithms are often studied in this field.
